00:01:44.304 --> 00:01:45.138
- Go go go go!

00:01:45.138 --> 00:01:45.972
(glass breaks)

00:01:45.972 --> 00:01:47.006
(siren wailing)

00:01:47.006 --> 00:01:47.707
- Oh my God!
- Go, go go!

00:01:47.707 --> 00:01:48.508
The pizza!

00:01:48.508 --> 00:01:49.342
- Leave it!

00:01:49.342 --> 00:01:50.176
(siren wailing)

00:01:50.176 --> 00:01:51.010
(horn honking)

00:01:51.010 --> 00:01:53.179
(crash sound)

00:01:53.179 --> 00:01:54.914
- At one point when
we were rewriting it,

00:01:54.914 --> 00:01:57.183
we were like, what
are we even saying?

00:01:57.183 --> 00:01:59.119 align:start size:84% position:16%
You know, in Sliding
Doors it's like,

00:01:59.119 --> 00:02:00.987 align:start size:94% position:6%
if you see the truth
it's better, but you die?

00:02:00.987 --> 00:02:02.622 align:start size:97% position:3%
- What are we even saying?
- I forget how the movie ends.

00:02:02.622 --> 00:02:03.823
- I love that though.
- But we were like,

00:02:03.823 --> 00:02:04.924
we're friends either way.

00:02:04.924 --> 00:02:06.192
- A new friend.

00:02:08.561 --> 00:02:12.165 align:start size:97% position:3%
- The version where we're
apart, it is an upsetting day,

00:02:12.165 --> 00:02:14.434
